The paper discusses data structures for approximate set membership queries, which is a topic in computer science related to data structures and algorithms. Specifically, the paper proposes a new data structure called the xor filter, which is compared to existing data structures such as Bloom and cuckoo filters. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Other likely categories include cs.DB (Databases), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing), and cs.IT (Information Theory), as these categories also deal with topics related to data structures and algorithms.
